content.step1: Preheat oven to 350Â°F. Grease two 8-inch round pans, line with parchment.
content.step2: Mix 1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour, 1 cup granulated sugar, 2 teaspoons baking powder.
content.step3: In another bowl, whisk 1/2 cup unsweetened cocoa powder, 1/2 cup whole milk, 2 large eggs.
content.step4: Combine wet and dry ingredients, mix until smooth, then add 1/4 cup vegetable oil.
content.step5: Divide batter evenly between prepared pans, bake for 30-35 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
content.step6: Let cool, then frost with chocolate buttercream and decorate as desired for serving.
